.TH "ps3_lpm_open" 9 "ps3_lpm_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ps3_lpm_open \- Open the logical performance monitor device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ps3_lpm_open
.BI "(enum ps3_lpm_tb_type tb_type "  ","
.BI "void *tb_cache "  ","
.BI "u64 tb_cache_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tb_type" 12
Specifies the type of trace buffer lv1 should use for this lpm
instance, specified by one of enum ps3_lpm_tb_type.
.IP "tb_cache" 12
Optional user supplied buffer to use as the trace buffer cache.
If NULL, the driver will allocate and manage an internal buffer.
Unused when when \fItb_type\fP is PS3_LPM_TB_TYPE_NONE.
.IP "tb_cache_size" 12
The size in bytes of the user supplied \fItb_cache\fP buffer.
Unused when \fItb_cache\fP is NULL or \fItb_type\fP is PS3_LPM_TB_TYPE_NONE.
